How to create new workbook including appointed worksheets using vba

1.new properties：

application.activeworkbook.name
application.activeworkbook.path

using these we could get the current book name and path.

worksheets（array（“sheet1”，“sheet2”））.copy
application.activeworkbook.save filenane：=xxxx bookformat：= bbbb （save as new）
                          .saveas                                  （save as copy）

---------------

date ：returns the date （yyyy-mm-dd）
time：returns the time （hh-mm-ss）
now： returns date and time

---------------

exit statement：

exit sub （will not use the left sentences in sub）
exit function （will not use the left sentences in function）
exit for （this will exit the loop）

---------------

Class module field：

Public xxx As String
Public bbb As Boolean

Module static fiekd：

Public nnn As String
